article.headline: Shurna's 29 points help Wildcats reach school wins record
article.linkText: Cats rout Hawkeyes, set school record for wins
article.story: EVANSTON, Ill. -- John Shurna scored 18 of his 29 points in the first half to lead Northwestern to an easy 74-57 victory over Iowa on Thursday night. After suffering a 78-65 loss at Iowa on Feb. 10, Northwestern (18-10, 7-9 Big Ten) took a big lead in the opening minutes with a number of easy backdoor layups, then Shurna followed with a barrage of 3-pointers. Shurna, who entered the night fourth in scoring in the Big Ten, gave the Wildcats a 23-9 lead with back-to-back 3s and Luka Mirkovic extended the lead to 31-11 on a rebound basket. Northwestern made 11 of its first 14 field-goal attempts and shot 63 percent in the first half, taking a 39-19 halftime lead. Matt Gatens scored 15 points and Cully Payne added 10 for Iowa (9-19, 3-12).
